    "However, this transition took over 35 ns due to strong contact line pinning 20, 110 -i.e., the temporary immobilization of the three-phase (solid-liquid-vapor) contact line by local energy barriers and surface heterogeneities, which slowed down the relaxation process.",
    "These results confirm that the unresolved contact angle reflects genuine hydrophilic behavior.",
    "Accordingly, the work of adhesion is a preferable parameter for characterizing the interaction between a solid and a liquid due to its possibility of application to a wider range of interactions.",
    "Simulation results for the work of adhesion are presented on Figure 8, together with the solid-liquid interaction energy and the entropy gain.",
